make_pdf("07_project_plan.pdf", "Project Plan: E-Commerce Platform Migration", [
    ("1. Project Overview", "This project involves migrating the existing monolithic e-commerce platform to a microservices architecture on AWS. The current platform handles 2 million daily active users and processes approximately 50,000 orders per day. The migration must be completed with zero downtime and no data loss. Total project budget is $2.4 million over 18 months."),
    ("2. Phase 1: Assessment (Months 1-3)", "Conduct a thorough assessment of the existing system including: database schema analysis (PostgreSQL, 450 tables, 2.3TB), API inventory (312 endpoints), dependency mapping, and performance baseline. Deliverables include an architecture design document, risk assessment, and detailed migration plan. Team: 2 architects, 3 senior engineers, 1 DBA. Estimated cost: $380,000."),
    ("3. Phase 2: Core Services (Months 4-9)", "Build core microservices: User Service, Product Catalog, Order Management, Payment Processing, and Inventory Management. Each service will have its own database (database-per-service pattern). Inter-service communication via Apache Kafka for async events and gRPC for sync calls. API Gateway using Kong. Team: 4 backend engineers, 2 frontend engineers, 2 DevOps, 1 QA lead. Estimated cost: $920,000."),
    ("4. Phase 3: Data Migration (Months 10-13)", "Implement dual-write pattern to keep both old and new systems in sync during migration. Use AWS DMS for initial data migration and CDC (Change Data Capture) for ongoing sync. Data validation framework to compare records between old and new systems. Rollback plan: ability to switch back to monolith within 15 minutes. Team: 2 data engineers, 1 DBA, 2 backend engineers. Estimated cost: $540,000."),
    ("5. Phase 4: Cutover and Optimization (Months 14-18)", "Gradual traffic shifting using weighted routing: 10% to new system in month 14, 50% by month 15, 100% by month 16. Performance optimization and cost reduction in months 17-18. Decommission old system after 30-day observation period. Success criteria: p99 latency under 200ms, error rate below 0.1%, cost reduction of at least 30%. Team: full team. Estimated cost: $560,000."),
    ("6. Risk Register", "Key risks: (1) Data inconsistency during dual-write period - mitigation: automated reconciliation jobs running every 5 minutes. (2) Performance degradation during migration - mitigation: load testing at 3x peak traffic before each phase. (3) Team attrition - mitigation: knowledge sharing sessions and documentation requirements. (4) Budget overrun - mitigation: 15% contingency buffer ($360,000) included in total budget."),
])
 
